\nExtract from the minutes of the 42nd meeting of the managers of the Kiev branch of the laboratory ¹15 from 09.09.96\nPresent were: 

\nDirector of the network of research laboratories - Frankevich S.K.
\nHead of the Kiev Branch of Laboratory #15 - I.L. Karteevich.
\nDeputy Head of Kiev branch of laboratory ¹15 - Ah.G. Lavrikov.

\nDecided: to recognize the further workability of the Kiev branch of the laboratory ¹15 as incapable. Grounds: lack of financing, partial leakage of information on the laboratory developments, threat to the existence of other secret objects, distrust to the staff.

\nNext steps:
\n- Laboratory personnel are to immediately make copies of lab reports. Destroy the original classified documents;
\n- Transfer all available documents to Prof. Chubko K.P.;
\n- All personnel, starting from the head of the Kiev branch and ending with laboratory technicians and cleaners, to undergo procedure B, in order to further preserve the secrecy of developments. The procedure should be conducted at low power (~100 Jigowatts);
\n- In case any of the personnel resists, action should be taken;
\n- Monitor the mental state of the personnel for 3 months after the procedure B;
\n- The results of procedure B should be reported to Prof. Chubko K.P.

\nSecretary of the meeting

\nLavrentiev Ah.L.
